edu.drexel.cs.jah473.autocorrect

Class Trie

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.drexel.cs.jah473.autocorrect.Trie
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<String>, Collection<String>, Set<String>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Autocorrect

    public class Trie
extends Object
implements Set<String>, Collection<String>, Serializable
    Represents a dynamic trie data structure for maintaining a set of strings. Supports insertion, deletion, and lookup in O(m) time where m is the length of the string in question. This implementation can be expected to perform as well as or slightly better than TreeSet for large collections of strings and will also maintain a natural ordering as long as all strings in the collection are composed only of letters of the English alphabet.

    This class implements both the Collection and Set interfaces for strings.
    Author:
    Justin Horvitz

      • toArray

        public <T> T[] toArray(T[] a)
        Returns an array containing all of the valid words in this trie. The runtime type of the returned array is that of the specified array. If all of the elements in this trie fit in the specified array, it is returned therein. Otherwise, a new array is allocated with the runtime type of the specified array and the size of this trie.
        Specified by:
        toArray in interface Collection<String>
        Specified by:
        toArray in interface Set<String>
        Parameters:
        a - the array into which the elements of the list are to be stored, if it is big enough; otherwise, a new array of the same runtime type is allocated for this purpose
        Returns:
        an array containing the valid words in this trie
